  <div>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_osteopathic_council">General Osteopathic Council</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_regulatory_body">Regulatory Body</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_osteopathic_council">General Osteopathic Council</xref>:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <p>Registers qualified professionals</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Sets standards of osteopathic practice and conduct</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Assures the quality of osteopathic education</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Ensures Continuing Professional Development</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
Helps 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 with complaints about an 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_osteopath">Osteopath</xref>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
The aim of the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_osteopathic_council">General Osteopathic Council</xref>
 is to protect 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>, develop the osteopathic profession and promote an understanding of osteopathic care.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_osteopathic_council">General Osteopathic Council</xref>, see the 
